snippet.textDisplay: The only disappointment is that it isn't longer! As a 25 year old Liverpool fan I've always looked back on the legendary Liverpool sides that used to dominate the world. The days when the all red jersey would strike fear into the hearts of any opposition. Istanbul was one of the highlights of my life, but apart from that following Liverpool has mostly been a story of disappointment and frustration. We've been competitive sure, but it's the hope that kills you. Since this man - this god - has led the helm, everything has changed. Sure, the first few years we missed out on a few finals. But like all true Liverpool fans, you could feel it was right. You felt it was coming. Then Madrid happened and the fucking critics crawled back into their caves. He's assembled the best team in world football and connected the best fans in world football with them. You can't help but think the future looks very, very promising for us red men. Fucking get in!

snippet.textDisplay: This is the most wonderful, amazing news. Thank you Jürgen for everything you have done. After "Spanish" Liverpool I had to watch with great sadness as the legacy of our wonderful club was in tatters. Apart from that one amazing SSS season, never in the Champions League, never in the top four, and resigned to the sadness that like Aston Villa and other successful clubs of the past, I would spend the rest of my days reminiscing about the past rather than the present. You came to us with an energy and a passion that was infectious. You eradicated that negativity and replaced it with positivity and belief again. And you have built (with the owners and the recruitment team) an incredible squad that I am privileged to see play. Right club, right owners, right recruitment organisation and RIGHT manager. How often does the perfect storm come together like that? Maybe never again in my lifetime. So thank you from the bottom of my heart for continuing this adventure with us. YNWA

snippet.textDisplay: Please Jurgen and Michael Edwards, get a centre half and a left back pronto.  Both strong and leaders. We want to keep our steam going into Feb-March. Buy them cheap but please get someone. If Virgil gets injured ( and he will one day , with our playing style and schedule), we will have 0 leaders at the back. We all know that Matip on his own is poor and Dejan screws up in the clutch moments.  Both up their performance with Virgil. Imagine having a centre-half like Koulibaly playing alongside Virgil. Someone strong and taking charge in the Dutchman's absence.  We have enough attackers to take care of the goalscoring. Liverpool have never won the title because they have always neglected the back five. Its twice recently when we've lost the lead after January. Even Jurgen messed about with Mignolet, Karius and some stupid defenders before getting sensible. Dejan Lovren is slow, reads the game poorly and comes off worse against good strikers. Please sell him.
